race.comment: The apprentices do battle here and there is generally more speed that what there might look on paper. ROCKTAGON (3) has been freshened up for this, having caught the eye late when running on at Murray Bridge last start. The chance of a wet track and getting onto a track like this are question marks but he can win. REINE OF NINE (8) drops in class after an OK effort in stronger city class last time. Looks ready to tick the 1200m box and can be finishing in the money. SILVER CHAOS (6) is a progressive mare that is drawn well and will enjoy any sting out of the ground. She's worth some thought, as is I LOVERAIN (2) whose form is hard to knock this preparation.
